{
  "stem": "15732.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The same way that also the ghettos of Germany, they sometimes could buy themself out, not often.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was already tradition to think always for a rainy day, or what tomorrow will bring, and have something beside to buy your-- your life out.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGH] It was a very, very painful state.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When they-- first of all, that when they came in, they-- pardon me-- they nationalized all private property.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That means my father had acquired several buildings and so on, that all was taking off, that was nationalized, because you couldn't have personal [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] goods-- building or something like that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father got a heart attack and was long, long weeks was sick because of the situation.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Our whole life was destabilized because of Communism and how do you adapt yourself to a new surrounding, a new political system that was always on guard of destabilizing us.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You see, they always-- everyone seemed to have been enlisted to tell on the other by the-- by the security.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Basically, not going into too many details, it-- it was a very unsettling time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were only a year under the Soviets, because eight days after the beginning of World War II, they retreated and we had German occupation.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But our luck is that it was not German occupation, it was Romanian [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "German. ?] The Germans went further into Russia, in the Romanians stayed and took back [INAUDIBLE] that they a year before had to give up for the Russians.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they took back their administration.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If it wouldn't have been their administration, I wouldn't be alive today to-- to talk.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had the-- the awful-- the awful privilege of seeing those murderers come again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were very well organized.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were very well-- even in retreat.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
